rmative and contentious interactions between ideas of human rights, rights of citizenship, and the concrete and envisioned social relationships that form the basis for social activism in the wake of neoliberalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aHuman rightsxArgentina. 0aHuman rightszArgentina. 0aNeoliberalismxArgentina. 0aNeoliberalismzArgentina. 0aPolitical rightsxArgentina. 0aPolitical rightszArgentina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478391040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804783910423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804783910.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles